1
00:00:06,363 --> 00:00:08,690
You clean up very nicely,
if you don't mind me saying so.

2
00:00:09,366 --> 00:00:12,268
I don't mind you saying so. Thanks.

3
00:00:14,309 --> 00:00:14,943
You look...

4
00:00:15,381 --> 00:00:18,350
pretty much the same as
you always look. Oh...

5
00:00:18,351 --> 00:00:19,751
Really? Yes.

6
00:00:20,050 --> 00:00:22,367
This is my date outfit. Really?

7
00:00:23,402 --> 00:00:24,484
Is this your first date?

8
00:00:24,604 --> 00:00:27,490
I mean, um, since your wife died?
Do I seem out of practice?

9
00:00:28,381 --> 00:00:29,347
Hi. Hi.

10
00:00:29,893 --> 00:00:32,063
Uh, my name's Gerard.
I'll be your server this evening.

11
00:00:32,064 --> 00:00:34,429
Would you like to hear our specials?
I'm sorry to interrupt, Gerard,

12
00:00:34,549 --> 00:00:36,862
but I'm getting a message from,
uh, your mother.

13
00:00:36,982 --> 00:00:42,021
A J-- no, um, Janis. Yes.

14
00:00:42,524 --> 00:00:43,874
Um...

15
00:00:45,012 --> 00:00:46,509
I'm sorry for your loss.

16
00:00:47,076 --> 00:00:48,565
She's happy now.

17
00:00:49,122 --> 00:00:52,248
And she wants you to know that
she sends her deepest love.

18
00:00:53,664 --> 00:00:55,389
And, um...

19
00:00:56,035 --> 00:00:57,445
your Uncle...

20
00:00:57,804 --> 00:01:00,700
Ed says, "Roll Tide."

21
00:01:01,217 --> 00:01:03,799
Does that mean anything
to you--Roll Tide?

22
00:01:05,250 --> 00:01:08,331
My mother's brother Edward.
He died five years ago.

23
00:01:08,451 --> 00:01:11,169
He was a tight end at
Alabama in the '60s. Oh.

24
00:01:11,633 --> 00:01:13,802
Uh, they're called
the Crimson Tide.

25
00:01:13,803 --> 00:01:16,570
Uh, that's their rallying cry-
"Roll Tide." Oh.

26
00:01:16,571 --> 00:01:18,572
Well, uh, I'd like to have

27
00:01:18,573 --> 00:01:21,801
the soup Du jour and
the lamb, medium,

28
00:01:22,060 --> 00:01:24,928
and the arugula salad and
the fish for the lady.

29
00:01:25,048 --> 00:01:26,013
Thank you. You're welcome.

30
00:01:26,014 --> 00:01:28,015
Thank you. Thank you.

31
00:01:28,016 --> 00:01:29,817
Thanks.

32
00:01:36,548 --> 00:01:38,862
What? Oh, come on.

33
00:01:40,012 --> 00:01:41,837
You're so ferocious
in your lack of faith.

34
00:01:42,398 --> 00:01:45,803
I mean, is it so hard to imagine
that I'm not putting on an act?

35
00:01:46,076 --> 00:01:48,358
That--that I really
am what I say I am?

36
00:01:49,192 --> 00:01:51,904
His mother sent a message.
I'm meant to help. That's all.

37
00:01:51,905 --> 00:01:54,674
It happens to me all the time.

38
00:01:55,795 --> 00:01:56,930
Okay.

39
00:01:58,478 --> 00:02:00,576
I'm sorry.

40
00:02:01,424 --> 00:02:02,717
Roll Tide.

41
00:02:14,208 --> 00:02:15,908
Bad guys just keep on coming, huh?

42
00:02:16,641 --> 00:02:17,859
I hate the Internet.

43
00:02:19,095 --> 00:02:20,518
Listen, if you like, I can deal.

44
00:02:20,638 --> 00:02:22,072
You go. No, it's okay.

45
00:02:22,192 --> 00:02:24,214
It's just a Web alert

46
00:02:24,334 --> 00:02:25,970
for when a name we're
interested in pops up.

47
00:02:35,875 --> 00:02:37,710
Wayne?

48
00:02:37,711 --> 00:02:39,378
What is it?

49
00:02:40,976 --> 00:02:43,015
Oh.

50
00:02:47,608 --> 00:02:49,434
This is not good.

51
00:02:49,554 --> 00:02:52,167
Relax, it's-- it's just a hoax.

52
00:02:52,742 --> 00:02:54,778
It's staged, almost certainly.

53
00:03:15,090 --> 00:03:17,347
I didn't put-- uh, no. Yes.

54
00:03:17,348 --> 00:03:18,712
No. No.

55
00:03:18,832 --> 00:03:20,901
You went to jail,
really? Yes, I did.

56
00:03:21,021 --> 00:03:22,587
What's so hard to believe?
For how long?

57
00:03:22,707 --> 00:03:25,055
I was there for two days and
two very luxurious nights.

58
00:03:25,175 --> 00:03:26,806
Uh-huh. Yeah.

59
00:03:26,926 --> 00:03:28,744
And how'd you get out?
I just escaped.

60
00:03:28,864 --> 00:03:30,951
Uh-huh. I don't believe you
for one second. It wasn't--

61
00:03:31,071 --> 00:03:33,684
it wasn't that difficult.
It's all timing.

62
00:03:33,804 --> 00:03:35,486
Uh-huh.

63
00:03:35,606 --> 00:03:38,533
I'm not kidding. Okay. -Huh.

64
00:03:38,534 --> 00:03:39,827
Excuse me. I have to
go to the bathroom.

65
00:03:46,285 --> 00:03:48,977
Ah, thank you.

66
00:04:37,723 --> 00:04:40,173
Hey.

67
00:04:44,240 --> 00:04:46,597
Kristina, um...

68
00:04:47,833 --> 00:04:50,418
Oh. I'm so sorry.

69
00:04:51,079 --> 00:04:52,942
It's work.

70
00:04:53,062 --> 00:04:55,376
Hello. Jane, you need to come

71
00:04:55,496 --> 00:04:58,107
to the office right now.

72
00:05:38,707 --> 00:05:40,734
It was posted on the
Internet an hour ago

73
00:05:40,854 --> 00:05:43,177
on a popular notice board.
There's a message

74
00:05:43,297 --> 00:05:45,250
that goes with it.

75
00:05:45,251 --> 00:05:47,260
"I am becoming what
I was meant to be.

76
00:05:47,380 --> 00:05:49,693
Your children's children
will worship me."

77
00:05:50,052 --> 00:05:51,721
We don't know when or
where the video was made.

78
00:05:51,841 --> 00:05:54,624
There appears to be an '08
Silverado parked outside the house,

79
00:05:54,744 --> 00:05:56,408
so it's gotta be at
least that recent.

80
00:05:57,202 --> 00:05:58,823
Has Red John made videos

81
00:05:58,943 --> 00:06:00,662
or issued statements
like this before? No.

82
00:06:01,036 --> 00:06:04,383
Oh, thank you. Excuse me.
Sorry to interrupt.

83
00:06:04,936 --> 00:06:07,971
Oh. Hi, Kristina.
Uh, good to see you.

84
00:06:09,323 --> 00:06:10,774
Yeah. That poor girl.

85
00:06:10,775 --> 00:06:12,476
Yeah, yeah.

86
00:06:12,852 --> 00:06:14,074
For what it's worth,

87
00:06:14,194 --> 00:06:16,704
I'm getting a sense that
she died very recently.

88
00:06:17,005 --> 00:06:21,078
Her body will be discovered very soon.
She's near water.

89
00:06:24,114 --> 00:06:26,222
Does this feel like
Red John to you?

90
00:06:26,747 --> 00:06:28,724
Uh, I'm not getting a read on that.

91
00:06:29,305 --> 00:06:32,123
The whole Internet aspect is
interesting, though, isn't it?

92
00:06:32,243 --> 00:06:33,170
I mean, why put it up there?

93
00:06:33,290 --> 00:06:36,055
This clip's had over a million viewers.
A desire for fame?

94
00:06:38,084 --> 00:06:39,444
Patrick, you're being very quiet.

95
00:06:39,564 --> 00:06:41,111
What are you thinking?

96
00:06:41,231 --> 00:06:42,986
Uh, I'd have to see
the crime scene.

97
00:06:43,106 --> 00:06:45,607
C.H.P. just reported a
homicide in the Bay area.

98
00:06:45,608 --> 00:06:46,975
Smiley face on the wall.

99
00:06:47,095 --> 00:06:48,954
College student named
Marley Sparrow.

100
00:06:49,074 --> 00:06:50,970
Roommate found her,
called it in about a half-hour ago.

101
00:06:51,660 --> 00:06:53,595
Let's get ready to go.

102
00:06:54,852 --> 00:06:55,716
Bay area?

103
00:06:55,717 --> 00:06:57,256
Uh, yes. That is close to water.

104
00:06:57,376 --> 00:06:58,868
That's, uh, that's uncanny.

105
00:06:58,988 --> 00:07:00,793
Oh, come on. That's pretty good.

106
00:07:01,382 --> 00:07:03,889
I am feeling a strong
connection to this case somehow.

107
00:07:04,134 --> 00:07:05,786
Madeline, can we
have a word, please

108
00:07:06,720 --> 00:07:07,991
Yeah.

109
00:07:08,111 --> 00:07:09,795
Excuse us.

110
00:07:12,400 --> 00:07:14,337
She's gonna ask if she
can come along with us.

111
00:07:14,581 --> 00:07:17,273
Now obviously, that's your call.
But I hope that you refuse,

112
00:07:17,949 --> 00:07:20,439
because I won't work with her.
I will quit.

113
00:07:20,440 --> 00:07:23,442
What's your objection?
If she can help us, why not?

114
00:07:23,443 --> 00:07:25,810
Nothing she says is more
than clever guesswork.

115
00:07:26,480 --> 00:07:29,046
So she has essentially
the same skills as you,

116
00:07:29,909 --> 00:07:31,878
without all the drama.

117
00:07:32,762 --> 00:07:34,452
What's the deal?

118
00:07:35,439 --> 00:07:37,388
Red John is mine.

119
00:07:40,025 --> 00:07:43,194
Okay. Okay, I hear you. Thank you.

120
00:07:43,195 --> 00:07:45,029
I'm sorry to interrupt.

121
00:07:45,030 --> 00:07:46,997
Oh, please. Uh...

122
00:07:48,733 --> 00:07:51,668
Um, I was going to
offer my services,

123
00:07:51,669 --> 00:07:52,820
but I get the sense

124
00:07:52,940 --> 00:07:55,196
Mr. Jane is telling you
that he won't work with me.

125
00:07:56,978 --> 00:07:59,842
The last thing I want to do
is upset this investigation,

126
00:08:00,437 --> 00:08:02,312
but if I have any more
feelings about the case,

127
00:08:02,313 --> 00:08:04,498
could I call you? Of course,
Kristina.

128
00:08:05,131 --> 00:08:06,496
Always be glad to
hear your thoughts.

129
00:08:07,588 --> 00:08:09,816
Have a good night. Thank you.

130
00:08:10,987 --> 00:08:12,321
Okay.

131
00:08:16,093 --> 00:08:18,428
Listen, uh, I-
I completely understand.

132
00:08:18,548 --> 00:08:21,097
No hard feelings. Okay.

133
00:08:23,399 --> 00:08:24,966
That was an unusual date,
though, huh?

134
00:08:24,967 --> 00:08:26,880
<i>Yes, very. Thank you.</i>

135
00:08:28,204 --> 00:08:30,031
I'll see you soon, I hope.

136
00:08:34,543 --> 00:08:36,427
Um, would you-- oh, yeah, sure.

137
00:08:37,379 --> 00:08:39,846
Oh.

138
00:08:42,584 --> 00:08:44,418
Bye. Bye.

139
00:08:56,771 --> 00:08:58,264
Guys give me a minute, please.

140
00:09:00,501 --> 00:09:02,502
Thank you.

141
00:09:19,418 --> 00:09:22,420
Hey, Marley. We'll get
this sorted out for you.

142
00:09:46,377 --> 00:09:48,378
Hey, hey, Patrick Jane.

143
00:09:48,878 --> 00:09:50,713
Long time.

144
00:09:50,714 --> 00:09:52,615
So qué pasa, dude?

145
00:09:53,264 --> 00:09:55,147
My people need to do their thing.

146
00:09:55,391 --> 00:09:57,119
I won't be long.

147
00:09:57,120 --> 00:09:58,453
Oh.

148
00:10:05,474 --> 00:10:09,298
You hoovering up the, uh,
ol' psychic ectoplasm?

149
00:10:11,901 --> 00:10:14,218
Yeah, that's exactly
what I'm doing.

150
00:10:15,261 --> 00:10:17,838
We have a schedule to keep,
amigo. Ticktock.

151
00:10:17,839 --> 00:10:19,322
Sooner you're done fooling around,

152
00:10:19,442 --> 00:10:21,729
sooner my people can
find actual clues.

153
00:10:22,447 --> 00:10:24,081
She's from Iowa.

154
00:10:25,202 --> 00:10:28,482
She played the guitar.
She liked dark chocolate,

155
00:10:28,483 --> 00:10:31,251
sudoku and snowboarding.

156
00:10:32,084 --> 00:10:33,620
Shy, but strong.

157
00:10:34,265 --> 00:10:35,745
Honorable, modest.

158
00:10:36,162 --> 00:10:37,991
Didn't drink or smoke.

159
00:10:38,923 --> 00:10:40,961
Parents died when
she was very young.

160
00:10:40,962 --> 00:10:43,014
And after college,
she wanted to go into family law

161
00:10:43,134 --> 00:10:44,770
and help foster kids like herself.

162
00:10:45,014 --> 00:10:48,801
Or become a singer.
She hadn't made up her mind yet.

163
00:10:48,802 --> 00:10:51,670
Yeah, that's great, dude.
But where's Red John?

164
00:10:51,671 --> 00:10:53,740
Oh, this wasn't Red John.

165
00:10:53,741 --> 00:10:56,075
So you say.

166
00:10:57,544 --> 00:10:59,545
So I say.

167
00:11:02,149 --> 00:11:04,149
Jerk.

168
00:11:04,721 --> 00:11:06,802
Oh, make sure you have your people

169
00:11:06,922 --> 00:11:09,669
send those papers and
journals to the CBI office.

170
00:11:09,997 --> 00:11:12,290
Will do. Thank you.

171
00:11:30,893 --> 00:11:32,643
Marley was the best.

172
00:11:32,644 --> 00:11:34,178
The best person.

173
00:11:34,179 --> 00:11:36,312
A beautiful soul.

174
00:11:36,313 --> 00:11:38,181
Rut you found her body, yes?

175
00:11:39,322 --> 00:11:40,449
When you entered your house,

176
00:11:40,450 --> 00:11:43,186
did you notice anything unusual
before you found the body?

177
00:11:43,187 --> 00:11:45,989
Something missing or out of place? No,
I don't think so.

178
00:11:45,990 --> 00:11:48,892
How long had you been gone?
Two days, snowboarding.

179
00:11:49,527 --> 00:11:50,893
Marley was supposed to come,

180
00:11:50,894 --> 00:11:53,495
but then her boyfriend was
coming over to see her,

181
00:11:53,496 --> 00:11:55,563
so she stayed. Boyfriend's name?

182
00:11:55,564 --> 00:11:58,901
Grady Shipp. He's a
policeman in San Francisco.

183
00:12:00,164 --> 00:12:02,973
They've been dating for,
like, a month.

184
00:12:03,548 --> 00:12:05,440
Okay. What was he like? Nice guy?

185
00:12:05,441 --> 00:12:07,287
Marley really liked him a lot.

186
00:12:07,646 --> 00:12:09,085
Said he was super nice

187
00:12:09,205 --> 00:12:11,956
but I don't know.
We never actually met him. No?

188
00:12:12,373 --> 00:12:14,480
She'd go to his place, mostly.

189
00:12:14,868 --> 00:12:16,575
And when he came by here,

190
00:12:16,695 --> 00:12:18,085
he'd wait for her in his car.

191
00:12:18,086 --> 00:12:19,821
Weird, no?

192
00:12:19,822 --> 00:12:21,989
I think Marley was
a bit embarrassed

193
00:12:21,990 --> 00:12:25,258
for hooking up with a cop,
you know? Ah.

194
00:12:25,259 --> 00:12:28,228
So she kept him on the down low.
Embarrassed, why?

195
00:12:28,963 --> 00:12:30,745
Marley was cool.

196
00:12:32,165 --> 00:12:34,824
And, well, cops are sort of
nerds with guns, aren't they?

197
00:12:34,944 --> 00:12:37,103
Ruth, hello?

198
00:12:38,167 --> 00:12:39,647
No offense.

199
00:12:40,707 --> 00:12:42,936
Sorry.

200
00:12:43,056 --> 00:12:44,944
Marley Sparrow?

201
00:12:44,945 --> 00:12:48,247
Yes, I was her academic
advisor for two semesters.

202
00:12:48,248 --> 00:12:49,687
Nice enough girl,

203
00:12:49,807 --> 00:12:52,852
but not as clever as she
likes to think she is.

204
00:12:53,213 --> 00:12:55,053
But none of 'em are, are they? Ha!

205
00:12:55,054 --> 00:12:57,222
Did you notice any changes
in her behavior recently?

206
00:12:57,223 --> 00:12:59,690
No. But nor do I pay
close attention.

207
00:12:59,691 --> 00:13:02,042
They're all empty vessels
to be filled with knowledge.

208
00:13:02,162 --> 00:13:04,401
Here is a horrible coincidence.

209
00:13:04,918 --> 00:13:08,599
Last semester, I taught
a criminology elective.

210
00:13:08,600 --> 00:13:12,770
Murder, myth and marketing-
the serial killer as commodity.

211
00:13:14,219 --> 00:13:18,407
Red John was actually mentioned
in our class discussions.

212
00:13:18,527 --> 00:13:21,011
Isn't that eerie? Who mentioned him?
What'd they say?

213
00:13:21,012 --> 00:13:23,375
Oh, damned if I know.
It was eight or nine months ago.

214
00:13:23,495 --> 00:13:24,829
Do you have a student
list from the class?

215
00:13:24,949 --> 00:13:27,983
You know, I do. I do. Somewhere.

216
00:13:29,653 --> 00:13:33,256
I do... We would love to
get a look at that list.

217
00:13:36,326 --> 00:13:38,294
Thanks.

218
00:13:39,561 --> 00:13:41,330
So there's no Grady Shipp with
any San Fran police agency.

219
00:13:41,331 --> 00:13:44,060
There's no Grady Shipp, period.
There was a Grady Shipp once.

220
00:13:44,180 --> 00:13:45,806
He killed and ate his
next-door neighbors

221
00:13:45,926 --> 00:13:47,861
in Little Rock back in the '90s.
He was lethally injected

222
00:13:47,981 --> 00:13:49,484
by the state of Arkansas in '02.

223
00:13:49,604 --> 00:13:51,688
Huh. So Marley's boyfriend
doesn't want anybody

224
00:13:51,808 --> 00:13:54,190
to see his face, and he named
himself after a cannibal.

225
00:13:54,621 --> 00:13:55,814
That's two strikes against him.

226
00:13:55,934 --> 00:13:57,248
Shame we don't have a
name or a description.

227
00:13:57,368 --> 00:13:59,284
The roommate, Ruth, said that
he never got out of his car.

228
00:13:59,404 --> 00:14:01,232
Maybe we can get a make
and model from her.

229
00:14:01,352 --> 00:14:02,898
Grady Shipp.

230
00:14:03,942 --> 00:14:08,204
In 1989, he did a 6-month spell
in the same wing at Lompoc

231
00:14:08,324 --> 00:14:09,424
as Orval Tanner.

232
00:14:09,425 --> 00:14:11,091
Orval Tanner? Red John's friend.

233
00:14:11,092 --> 00:14:14,234
You have the entire Lompoc
prison registry in your head?

234
00:14:14,354 --> 00:14:16,353
Well, only the relevant sections.

235
00:14:16,655 --> 00:14:18,320
Wh-what does it mean? Is it a joke?

236
00:14:18,440 --> 00:14:20,016
Marley's boyfriend is Red John.

237
00:14:20,136 --> 00:14:21,987
That doesn't make any sense.

238
00:14:23,365 --> 00:14:26,306
<i>In the hunt for this beast known as "
Red John."</i>

239
00:14:28,342 --> 00:14:30,510
<i>Well, he-- he's not a beast, Jackie.</i>

240
00:14:30,511 --> 00:14:32,478
<i>He's a human being.</i>

241
00:14:32,479 --> 00:14:34,513
<i>Now he has done terrible thing</i>

242
00:14:34,514 --> 00:14:38,317
<i>bubuhe is still capable of redemption...
like all of us.</i>

243
00:14:41,822 --> 00:14:44,926
<i>Red John...</i>

244
00:14:45,832 --> 00:14:47,152
<i>If you're listening to us now,</i>

245
00:14:47,272 --> 00:14:49,872
<i>I urge you to reach out and get help.</i>

246
00:14:50,835 --> 00:14:53,364
<i>You can change.</i>

247
00:15:08,051 --> 00:15:09,818
What the hell are you thinking?!

248
00:15:09,819 --> 00:15:11,987
Don't you understand who
you're dealing with?

249
00:15:11,988 --> 00:15:14,188
I do understand, yes.
No, you don't.

250
00:15:14,189 --> 00:15:16,257
Clearly, you don't understand.

251
00:15:16,258 --> 00:15:17,672
I asked miss Frye here

252
00:15:17,792 --> 00:15:19,896
so that I could fully
express my deep dismay.

253
00:15:20,212 --> 00:15:21,609
I was speaking from the heart.

254
00:15:21,729 --> 00:15:24,239
That may be, but you were
also hustling for business.

255
00:15:24,359 --> 00:15:27,536
And that's okay, but you
present me now with a problem.

256
00:15:28,621 --> 00:15:30,692
We don't have any obligation
to protect you, but--

257
00:15:30,812 --> 00:15:33,610
I wasn't asking for protection.
It's completely unnecessary.

258
00:15:33,730 --> 00:15:35,244
Red John is not coming after me.

259
00:15:35,364 --> 00:15:37,840
Are you blind? You've
done exactly what I did.

260
00:15:38,415 --> 00:15:41,255
I went on television and talked
about him as though I knew him,

261
00:15:41,375 --> 00:15:43,043
and he killed my wife and child.

262
00:15:43,316 --> 00:15:46,443
Patrick, he was punishing you
because you lied about him.

263
00:15:47,133 --> 00:15:49,934
I was telling the truth.
He won't take offense with me.

264
00:15:50,503 --> 00:15:51,897
He might even listen
to what I said.

265
00:15:52,017 --> 00:15:54,060
In fact, I-I believe he will.

266
00:15:55,429 --> 00:15:57,764
People do change, Patrick.
It's possible.

267
00:15:59,767 --> 00:16:02,684
Agent Hightower, I'm truly
sorry for dismaying you.

268
00:16:05,071 --> 00:16:07,906
Now if you'll excuse me,
I have some other appointments.

269
00:16:12,946 --> 00:16:15,789
She needs 24-hour protection--

270
00:16:15,909 --> 00:16:17,595
the best that you can provide.

271
00:16:17,715 --> 00:16:20,152
The SAC P.D.
special protection unit

272
00:16:20,272 --> 00:16:21,952
will provide security,
the CBI will be

273
00:16:22,072 --> 00:16:23,854
on the inside,
bodyguarding miss Frye.

274
00:16:23,974 --> 00:16:25,526
Jane and I will take
the first shift.

275
00:16:25,646 --> 00:16:27,999
The next 24-hour rotation
will be split among us,

276
00:16:28,119 --> 00:16:29,426
alternating with the Sparrow case.

277
00:16:29,635 --> 00:16:31,447
Well, we're gonna have to stop
protecting her sooner or later.

278
00:16:31,567 --> 00:16:33,396
That's when he'll go for her.
He'll just wait.

279
00:16:33,655 --> 00:16:35,179
Van Pelt, what do you got?

280
00:16:35,299 --> 00:16:37,634
We're looking for
Grady Shipp, right?

281
00:16:37,635 --> 00:16:39,706
This is Marley's address book.
That's different writing.

282
00:16:39,826 --> 00:16:42,089
Maybe that's Grady
Shipp himself. Can I?

283
00:16:42,209 --> 00:16:45,190
Keep digging. Rigsby, take Cho with you.
Check it out. Yeah, you got it.

284
00:16:51,815 --> 00:16:54,383
Hello?

285
00:17:05,662 --> 00:17:08,663
Lapping sounds)

286
00:17:13,079 --> 00:17:15,337
Hello?

287
00:17:45,299 --> 00:17:47,300
Blood. Yep.

288
00:17:49,703 --> 00:17:52,071
Pig's blood, maybe.

289
00:17:52,072 --> 00:17:53,839
For practice?

290
00:18:08,087 --> 00:18:09,754
Police! Stop!

291
00:18:12,491 --> 00:18:14,492
Police! Stop!

292
00:18:29,773 --> 00:18:31,774
I'll call it in.

293
00:18:38,449 --> 00:18:39,916
What is it?

294
00:18:39,917 --> 00:18:41,984
A lens cap.

295
00:18:41,985 --> 00:18:43,485
Interesting.

296
00:18:43,486 --> 00:18:45,489
Practicing the Red John symbol,

297
00:18:45,609 --> 00:18:47,923
and not just watching
us pursue him,

298
00:18:47,924 --> 00:18:49,925
but filming the pursuit.

299
00:18:50,319 --> 00:18:51,993
What does it mean?

300
00:18:51,994 --> 00:18:55,097
It means Marley Sparrow's killer
loves cameras. He's a voyeur...

301
00:18:55,098 --> 00:18:56,228
A fanboy,

302
00:18:56,348 --> 00:18:57,698
a slasher movie geek. Huh.

303
00:18:57,818 --> 00:19:00,054
Great. But where does
that take us now?

304
00:19:00,299 --> 00:19:03,906
Like in a car? Well,
try the campus film club.

305
00:19:04,424 --> 00:19:06,292
All right.

306
00:19:07,142 --> 00:19:09,443
Nice place, huh? Tasteful.

307
00:19:09,946 --> 00:19:12,146
To me, it looks like we're
about to pay way too much money

308
00:19:12,147 --> 00:19:14,149
to get our legs waxed. Hmm.

309
00:19:14,269 --> 00:19:16,821
Hi. I was just making some lunch.

310
00:19:16,941 --> 00:19:18,885
Would you like something to eat?
Sure, thanks.

311
00:19:18,886 --> 00:19:21,555
I'm good. Thanks.

312
00:19:21,556 --> 00:19:24,722
Patrick, uh, on reflection,

313
00:19:24,842 --> 00:19:27,294
I'm truly sorry for the
situation I put you in.

314
00:19:27,295 --> 00:19:28,861
I hadn't thought through
your involvement.

315
00:19:28,981 --> 00:19:30,764
All right, all right.
I-I-I'll eat some lunch.

316
00:19:30,884 --> 00:19:32,831
Just please don't make a fuss.

317
00:19:34,507 --> 00:19:36,044
Miss Ketchum?

318
00:19:36,164 --> 00:19:38,137
Oh, policemen.

319
00:19:38,438 --> 00:19:41,746
Okay. I knew I'd forgotten
something. Uh...

320
00:19:41,866 --> 00:19:43,407
Okay.

321
00:19:43,838 --> 00:19:45,344
There it is.

322
00:19:45,345 --> 00:19:47,106
I thought for sure I'd sent that.

323
00:19:47,226 --> 00:19:49,079
Sent what? Uhuh, the class list

324
00:19:49,199 --> 00:19:51,318
of the students in
my criminology class.

325
00:19:52,052 --> 00:19:53,685
Your colleague had asked for it.

326
00:19:53,686 --> 00:19:55,420
And you're chair of
the film club also?

327
00:19:55,421 --> 00:19:58,173
I have that honor. You know what?

328
00:19:58,293 --> 00:20:00,625
I have the film club
register here as well.

329
00:20:00,626 --> 00:20:02,093
Okay...

330
00:20:02,094 --> 00:20:05,061
Yes, yes. Would you like to see it?

331
00:20:05,062 --> 00:20:07,364
Yes. That would be, uh, good.

332
00:20:07,365 --> 00:20:09,032
Okay.

333
00:20:09,033 --> 00:20:11,001
Ah, there you go.

334
00:20:14,855 --> 00:20:16,707
And where were you Tuesday night,
miss Ketchum?

335
00:20:18,410 --> 00:20:20,777
<i>Oh, how thrilling!</i>

336
00:20:20,778 --> 00:20:23,313
Am I a suspect? Are you?

337
00:20:23,314 --> 00:20:25,315
Well...

338
00:20:25,316 --> 00:20:28,351
I'd like to think I can still
summon that kind of passion.

339
00:20:28,352 --> 00:20:30,821
So where were you?

340
00:20:30,822 --> 00:20:32,823
Home. Alone.

341
00:20:32,824 --> 00:20:34,890
Reading a murder mystery, actually.

342
00:20:34,891 --> 00:20:37,927
Now there's only one name on
both lists--Wesley Blankfein.

343
00:20:37,928 --> 00:20:40,196
Oh, wait. You just made a face.

344
00:20:41,286 --> 00:20:43,165
Well, he is a sweet boy.

345
00:20:43,166 --> 00:20:45,430
Rather a good actor, actually.

346
00:20:46,399 --> 00:20:48,237
But, uh... strange.

347
00:20:48,238 --> 00:20:51,272
Strange? How? I can't
really put my finger on it.

348
00:20:51,273 --> 00:20:53,842
It's a look in his eyes.

349
00:20:53,843 --> 00:20:55,576
Yep, that's him.

350
00:20:56,051 --> 00:20:57,545
I remember when he moved in.

351
00:20:57,546 --> 00:20:59,080
I mentioned to him

352
00:20:59,081 --> 00:21:00,787
he was a little older
than most of our students,

353
00:21:01,086 --> 00:21:03,774
and he said he needed to
escape from his mother.

354
00:21:05,971 --> 00:21:08,330
Which, uh, I thought
was an odd response.

355
00:21:08,450 --> 00:21:11,430
And when did you last see him? Uh,
three weeks ago...

356
00:21:11,550 --> 00:21:14,219
Excuse me. Uh, maybe.
I figured he had a girlfriend.

357
00:21:14,886 --> 00:21:17,023
Nothin here. Oh, hey, Dylan.

358
00:21:17,807 --> 00:21:19,032
Oh, hey, you guys. Quick question.

359
00:21:19,337 --> 00:21:20,633
Now you guys said
Marley's boyfriend

360
00:21:20,634 --> 00:21:22,802
waited for her outside
in a car? Yes.

361
00:21:22,803 --> 00:21:24,067
Do you recall what
type of car he drove?

362
00:21:24,187 --> 00:21:27,987
Um, it was black,  I think.
I'm bad with cars.

363
00:21:28,107 --> 00:21:29,782
It was a-- it was a black S.U.V.

364
00:21:30,156 --> 00:21:32,979
What car did Blankfein drive? Uh,
he didn't have a car.

365
00:21:34,848 --> 00:21:36,849
Huh. Okay.

366
00:21:36,850 --> 00:21:38,851
Try locating Blankfein's mother.

367
00:21:38,852 --> 00:21:40,818
Maybe she knows where he is.

368
00:21:41,320 --> 00:21:43,388
All right. Let me know.

369
00:21:43,389 --> 00:21:45,357
Wesley Blankfein's in the wind.

370
00:21:45,358 --> 00:21:48,093
Looks like he might be good for this.
I don't think so.

371
00:21:48,094 --> 00:21:49,822
Marley made contact with me.

372
00:21:49,942 --> 00:21:51,489
The name "Blankfein"
doesn't resonate.

373
00:21:51,805 --> 00:21:53,816
Marley made contact with you? Yes.

374
00:21:54,233 --> 00:21:56,742
Of course. Uh, I think

375
00:21:56,862 --> 00:22:00,004
we might have had enough of your
crime-fighting skills, Kristina.

376
00:22:00,501 --> 00:22:02,706
Might be best to stick
to the crystal therapy

377
00:22:02,707 --> 00:22:05,609
and the, uh... foot massages?

378
00:22:05,610 --> 00:22:07,378
Reflexology. Right.

379
00:22:07,379 --> 00:22:09,846
Reflexology.

380
00:22:12,082 --> 00:22:13,749
This is Lisbon.

381
00:22:13,750 --> 00:22:16,286
Agent Senton, FBI.
Yeah, we got a case

382
00:22:16,287 --> 00:22:17,668
here in Lake Tahoe.

383
00:22:18,141 --> 00:22:19,754
Looks like your boy Red John.

384
00:22:20,027 --> 00:22:21,120
Victim's name is

385
00:22:21,240 --> 00:22:23,156
a Jacqueline Sandoval.

386
00:22:23,794 --> 00:22:25,995
You wanna come take a look?

387
00:22:30,099 --> 00:22:31,934
You can smile your arrogant smile

388
00:22:31,935 --> 00:22:34,437
and act like you know
everything about everything,

389
00:22:34,438 --> 00:22:36,539
but you don't.
There are whole worlds

390
00:22:36,540 --> 00:22:39,379
that you can't even begin to understand.
Synchronized swimming

391
00:22:39,499 --> 00:22:41,744
is, uh, the only world
that Springs to mind.

392
00:22:41,745 --> 00:22:43,389
But I'm sure you're right.
There may be many others.

393
00:22:44,830 --> 00:22:46,583
What's the matter?

394
00:22:47,144 --> 00:22:49,414
Red John killed the woman
who interviewed you.

395
00:22:51,487 --> 00:22:53,254
Oh, my God.

396
00:22:57,319 --> 00:22:59,202
Oh, my God.

397
00:23:45,687 --> 00:23:47,588
It's Red John, all right.

398
00:23:47,589 --> 00:23:49,425
Okay, uh, I'll reach
out to the feds.

399
00:23:49,545 --> 00:23:52,258
I'll make sure they keep us in the loop.
We gotta get back to Kristina Frye's place.

400
00:23:52,378 --> 00:23:55,104
There are cops all around her house.
Van Pelt is with her,

401
00:23:55,224 --> 00:23:57,885
and there's other CBI agents
on their way. She's safe.

402
00:23:58,590 --> 00:24:00,569
I am confident Red John's
not gonna go there.

403
00:24:00,689 --> 00:24:03,376
That is exactly why he might.
If he does, we'll get him.

404
00:24:04,253 --> 00:24:06,079
You really wanna hang
out at Kristina's house,

405
00:24:06,199 --> 00:24:07,511
waiting for Red John to show up?

406
00:24:07,631 --> 00:24:09,084
Let's just go back to the office,

407
00:24:09,204 --> 00:24:12,421
and we'll work the Marley Sparrow case.
There's nothing useful that I can do there.

408
00:24:12,541 --> 00:24:16,688
This Blankfein character-
he looks good for it, right? Fine.

409
00:24:16,683 --> 00:24:19,438
Go and wait for Red John.
It's not a good idea, though.

410
00:24:20,185 --> 00:24:21,620
Hey, we're in Nevada.

411
00:24:21,740 --> 00:24:25,158
You can't just walk
off and leave me here.

412
00:24:25,563 --> 00:24:27,801
Hey. Hey, boss.

413
00:24:27,997 --> 00:24:31,052
So Wesley Blankfein's mother
is Myra Hauser-Blankfein.

414
00:24:31,172 --> 00:24:32,698
Address in Franklin heights.

415
00:24:32,699 --> 00:24:34,558
And she owns a black S.U.V.
Like Grady Shipp drives.

416
00:24:34,678 --> 00:24:36,030
Good. Go check her out.

417
00:24:36,150 --> 00:24:37,724
Now? Well, it's a long drive.

418
00:24:38,170 --> 00:24:40,437
You leave now, you'll
be there by the morning.

419
00:25:01,292 --> 00:25:03,293
Grace, thank you.

420
00:25:08,867 --> 00:25:10,868
How you doing?

421
00:25:10,869 --> 00:25:14,069
I'm doing fine.

422
00:25:15,020 --> 00:25:17,391
Red John certainly made his point.

423
00:25:18,141 --> 00:25:21,586
Quite possibly,
he'll leave things be now.

424
00:25:22,145 --> 00:25:23,946
I know he will.

425
00:25:24,451 --> 00:25:26,148
I have a clear vision of him.

426
00:25:26,149 --> 00:25:28,487
He needs to create fear,
that's all.

427
00:25:28,875 --> 00:25:31,319
He's done that now,
and he feels calm.

428
00:25:31,320 --> 00:25:32,471
And I'm perfectly safe.

429
00:25:32,591 --> 00:25:35,044
Will you just stop that nonsense?

430
00:25:36,191 --> 00:25:38,154
You wanted to promote
your psychic business,

431
00:25:38,274 --> 00:25:39,813
and--and you made a big mistake.

432
00:25:39,933 --> 00:25:42,105
Now will you just-
will you please just own it?!

433
00:25:42,479 --> 00:25:43,513
Why are you here?

434
00:25:43,633 --> 00:25:45,561
I am here because I
want to protect you.

435
00:25:45,867 --> 00:25:47,305
And how are you gonna protect me?

436
00:25:47,607 --> 00:25:49,275
If Red John comes through
that door right now,

437
00:25:49,395 --> 00:25:52,305
what are you gonna do, hypnotize him?
I will do what I need to do.

438
00:25:53,067 --> 00:25:55,576
If Red John wants to
reach me, he will.

439
00:25:55,944 --> 00:25:58,047
I choose to believe
that he doesn't want to.

440
00:25:58,167 --> 00:26:00,981
Now please, go away. I'm gone.

441
00:26:16,630 --> 00:26:18,453
Uh, you're wasting your time.

442
00:26:18,573 --> 00:26:20,871
Ma'am, we're looking for Mrs.
Blankfein and her son. Gone.

443
00:26:20,991 --> 00:26:24,502
And left the cats to starve.
It's not right.

444
00:26:24,503 --> 00:26:27,806
Do you know where they went? Uh, nope.
Never leaves before. Never.

445
00:26:27,807 --> 00:26:30,019
Every day, 11:00,

446
00:26:30,139 --> 00:26:32,811
like a machine,
she's watching her TV shows.

447
00:26:32,812 --> 00:26:36,681
Three days now I hear nothing.
Quiet like the grave.

448
00:26:36,682 --> 00:26:38,469
How about her son Wesley?
Have you seen him?

449
00:26:38,589 --> 00:26:40,065
Nope. Gone, too.

450
00:26:40,185 --> 00:26:42,018
Did it occur to you that Mrs.
Blankfein might be dead in there?

451
00:26:42,138 --> 00:26:43,714
Yes, it did.

452
00:26:44,576 --> 00:26:47,272
But there'd be a smell,
wouldn't there, if she was dead?

453
00:26:50,771 --> 00:26:52,755
Step back inside, please, ma'am.

454
00:26:53,297 --> 00:26:55,431
You good? Yeah.

455
00:27:07,777 --> 00:27:10,178
Bedroom's clear.

456
00:27:11,002 --> 00:27:13,048
Rigsby.

457
00:27:16,519 --> 00:27:18,633
Oh, jeez.

458
00:27:19,946 --> 00:27:22,189
"G.S." Grady Shipp.

459
00:27:22,190 --> 00:27:24,325
Bingo.

460
00:27:26,061 --> 00:27:28,062
Inside the mind of
Wesley Blankfein--

461
00:27:28,063 --> 00:27:30,665
A.K.A. Grady Shipp. Not pretty.

462
00:27:30,666 --> 00:27:32,533
What it looks like--

463
00:27:32,534 --> 00:27:35,003
he's obsessed with Marley,
so he builds a shrine

464
00:27:35,004 --> 00:27:36,795
and he fakes up all these
photos of them together.

465
00:27:37,044 --> 00:27:38,939
Then he tries to turn the
fantasy into reality,

466
00:27:38,940 --> 00:27:41,151
and posing as Grady Shipp,
asks her out,

467
00:27:41,271 --> 00:27:44,379
and she says yes. Big mistake.
Fantasy and reality collide,

468
00:27:44,767 --> 00:27:46,971
and she dies. Sounds about right.

469
00:27:47,216 --> 00:27:49,440
Where the hell is he? Uh,
where's his mom?

470
00:27:49,742 --> 00:27:52,034
You didn't find anything useful in
the apartment? No computer, nothing?

471
00:27:52,154 --> 00:27:53,715
No. A lot of cats.

472
00:27:53,835 --> 00:27:55,334
Now the pictures of Marley-
they were all taken

473
00:27:55,454 --> 00:27:57,652
at different times and places.
The pictures of Wesley

474
00:27:57,772 --> 00:28:00,401
were all taken in the same place.
Nowhere we've been.

475
00:28:00,861 --> 00:28:03,304
Maybe that's a safe house for him.
Nothing to say where it is, though.

476
00:28:03,749 --> 00:28:08,481
Jane, you wanna take a look?
See if you see anything useful? Huh?

477
00:28:08,601 --> 00:28:10,082
Yeah, sure.

478
00:28:10,202 --> 00:28:12,603
If you like.

479
00:28:30,254 --> 00:28:32,241
Hmm.

480
00:28:32,361 --> 00:28:34,992
Yep. And...

481
00:28:34,993 --> 00:28:37,346
There's a photo of Wesley
with a sign in the distance--

482
00:28:37,466 --> 00:28:39,669
a yellow "kc" backward on a pole.

483
00:28:39,789 --> 00:28:41,785
His--his shadow is
pointing right to it.

484
00:28:45,277 --> 00:28:47,590
Yeah. It's way small back there,
but I see it.

485
00:28:48,251 --> 00:28:50,077
Yeah, that's the logo
for Kenny's Chili--

486
00:28:50,364 --> 00:28:52,078
Southern California
fast food chain.

487
00:28:52,351 --> 00:28:54,649
There's about 50 or so outlets.
You memorize trademarks?

488
00:28:54,769 --> 00:28:57,420
Well, with Wesley's long
shadow and the golden light,

489
00:28:57,540 --> 00:29:00,005
that would say afternoon.
And sun is in the West,

490
00:29:01,250 --> 00:29:04,285
so that puts Kenny's due
East of this location--

491
00:29:04,286 --> 00:29:06,722
about a block and a half, I'd say.

492
00:29:06,723 --> 00:29:08,380
Huh. He's right.

493
00:29:08,500 --> 00:29:11,618
50 or so outlets?
Hardware store and a liquor store

494
00:29:11,738 --> 00:29:14,139
on the block right next to it.
That should narrow it down.

495
00:29:14,446 --> 00:29:16,070
I'll get on it.

496
00:29:17,191 --> 00:29:19,343
Thank you. Oh. No.

497
00:29:20,809 --> 00:29:22,431
You should make that call.

498
00:29:23,471 --> 00:29:25,171
What call? Right.

499
00:29:25,291 --> 00:29:27,084
Like I'm not a Detective, too?

500
00:29:41,555 --> 00:29:43,830
Hey, Jane. It's Grace.

501
00:29:44,089 --> 00:29:46,558
Kristina's taking a nap.
I can get her for you if you l like.

502
00:29:46,678 --> 00:29:49,068
I'd appreciate that, Grace.
Thank you.

503
00:29:51,497 --> 00:29:53,465
Kristina?

504
00:29:54,933 --> 00:29:56,268
Kristina,

505
